#X text 50 129 You can create it from the menu "Put > Matrix" \, or the shortcut <cmd|ctrl> + <shift> + X \, or typing "radio" on an object box., f 64;
#X text 205 33 "radio" / Matrix;
#N canvas 806 182 551 370 interaction 0;
#X text 52 247 Use the "orientation" message to read them in row-major (horizontal) or column-major order.;
#X text 52 290 NOTE: columns \, rows \, and orientation can be set from the properties dialog;
#X text 55 62 In 2-d matrices \, the filled square represents the index to a column or row on the matrix \, depending on orientation., f 57;
#X text 55 115 If orientation is "horizontal" \, the index represents COLUMNS \, if it is "vertical" \, it represents the ROWS.;
#X text 53 165 For example \, in the horizontal case \, clicking on any row will move the filled square will remain on the first row \, but move to the corresponding COLUMN regardless of the actual row that was clicked.;
#X text 124 21 The filled square on row/column 1;
#X restore 124 531 pd interaction;
#X text 52 501 More information:;
#N canvas 959 188 450 300 properties 0;
#X text 12 62 "hradio" and "vradio" now have "Columns" \, "Rows" \, and "Orientation" on the properties dialog (check it out with right-click + Properties).;
#X text 9 146 If you change those to a 2d matrix \, the object will be saved as a "radio" and treated as such.;
#X text 133 30 New "properties" dialog;
#X restore 236 532 pd properties;
#X text 252 212 You can interact with it as the old radio (number switching when clicking) or by Shift + Clicking on the squares to set a cross., f 35;
#N canvas 1075 144 514 531 sizes 0;
#X text 37 66 When a "radio" is saved \, we check first if the object is 2d or 1d. If it's 1d \, it is either saved as "hradio" or "vradio" \, as before \, and its size is also stored as before \, in values from 1 up until 128 (the maximum allowed for h/vradio);
#X text 36 162 However \, when the radio is 2d \, we store it as a "radio" object \, and we encode the size and the orientation in the negative values \, which is why you will see a weird size like -259 \, which would decode to "3 x 3 horizontal radio". If you're curious \, check out the source code to see how this encoding/decoding works.;
#X text 35 279 Naturally \, this encoding is never shown to the user \, as they now see "Columns" and "Rows" in the properties dialog \, unless they open the .pd file and check it out.;
#X text 197 363 Max size;
#X text 46 394 For performance reasons \, the size is maxed out to 128 (the maximum allowed by hradio or vradio). So \, sizes are clamped so that we always have N x M <= 128 For example \, if Columns = 2 \, then Rows can only have values <= 64 \, or if Columns = 3 \, Rows can only have <= 42 \, etc.;
#X text 210 29 Saving;
#X restore 49 531 pd sizes;
#X text 253 288 Crosses are 1 \, empty squares are 0;
